  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).",
    "Season lamb chops with salt and pepper.",
    "Sauté garlic, onion, carrots, celery in olive oil until softened.",
    "Add tomato paste and cook for an additional minute.",
    "Pour in chicken broth and red wine. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer for 15 minutes.",
    "Fold in thyme sprigs and bay leaves. Add lamb chops and continue cooking for another 20-30 minutes or until tender.",
    "Let rest before serving as desired.",
    "Garnish with additional fresh herbs if preferred.",
    "Ensure poultry is cooked to an internal temperature of 74°C / 165°F (juices run clear, no pink remaining) before serving."
